The paper deals with 3D reconstruction and compression of human shapes using deep learning techniques. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of panoramic depth maps and autoencoder-based compression also suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the development of pixel-wise feature descriptors and end-to-end learning scheme indicates a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
